com.intel.icecp.module.jsengine

Class JSEngineModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.module.jsengine.JSEngineModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intel.icecp.core.Module

    @ModuleProperty(name="JSEngineModule",
                attributes=CodeAttribute.class)
public class JSEngineModule
extends Object
implements com.intel.icecp.core.Module
    This module will execute a Nashorn javascript file inside a ScriptEngine. A command channel is opened, and subscribed to. Send a JSEngineMessage to the channel, and it will execute the specified script.

    You can test this module by just creating a message, publish it to the command channel, and get the response:

    JSEngineMessage msg = new JSEngineMessage("MyNode", "return-channel");

    Channel<JSEngineMessage> channel = node.openChannel(...);

    channel.publish(msg);

    msg = channel.latest.get();

    if (msg.ranSuccessful)

    //success;
